UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: More children, including the most marginalized , are surviving, healthy, well nourished and developing to their full potential in their early years, with focus on the first 1,000 days

description.narrative: UNICEF&39;s immediate and coordinated support to the MoHSPP through the provision of technical supports, provision of essential vaccines and life-saving items, and capacity building of health workers contributed to timely management of COVID-19 cases, management of polio outbreak, and implementation of planned interventions and fulfillment of the commitments. UNICEF continued advocacy resulted in leveraging additional resources for Immunization and IPC projects. Completion of baseline assessments for the IPC project will provide a strong platform for implementation of key activities related to the provision of medical equipment and capacity building for health workers in 2022. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
